   "source": [
    "# Your First LLM-Powered Tool\n",
    "\n",
    "Starter notebook. Fill in the TODOs and **run every cell** before committing.\n",
    "Do **not** commit your API key — load it from `.env`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Setup\n",
    "# pip install -r requirements.txt\n",
    "import os, json\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "from google import genai\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv() # Load GEMINI_API_KEY from .env\n",
    "GEMINI_API_KEY = os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\")\n",
    "assert GEMINI_API_KEY, \"Set GEMINI_API_KEY (see .env.example)\"\n",
    "client = genai.Client(api_key=GEMINI_API_KEY)\n",
    "MODEL = \"gemini-2.0-flash\"\n"
    ],
    "cell_type": "code"
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 1 — First calls and the sampling dial\n",
    "\n",
    "Make a working call (print response **and token usage**), then send the same prompt 3× at temp ~0.1 and 3× at temp ~1.0.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "system_instruction = \"You are a concise support assistant.\"\n",
    "user_prompt = \"Explain what a support ticket is in one sentence.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. First call with usage metadata\n",
    "print(\"--- First Call ---\")\n",
    "response = client.models.generate_content(\n",
    "    model=MODEL,\n",
    "    config={'system_instruction': system_instruction},\n",
    "    contents=user_prompt\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Response: {response.text}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Usage: {response.usage_metadata}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Temperature loop\n",
    "for temp in [0.1, 1.0]:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n--- Temperature {temp} ---\")\n",
    "    for i in range(3):\n",
    "        response = client.models.generate_content(\n",
    "            model=MODEL,\n",
    "            config={\n",
    "                'system_instruction': system_instruction,\n",
    "                'temperature': temp\n",
    "            },\n",
    "            contents=user_prompt\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        print(f\"Run {i+1}: {response.text.strip()}\")\n"
    ],
    "cell_type": "code"
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**What changed, and why?**\n",
    "\n",
    "> At temperature 0.1, the outputs are highly consistent and often identical, as the model greedily picks the most likely tokens. At temperature 1.0, the outputs show more variety in phrasing and word choice, as the sampling distribution is 'flatter', allowing less probable but still relevant tokens to be selected, increasing creativity and randomness."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 2 — Prompt-pattern bake-off\n",
    "\n",
    "Classify the tickets three ways (zero-shot, few-shot, chain-of-thought) into `billing / bug / feature_request / other`. Build a comparison table. Record prompts + verdict in `prompts.md`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(\"tickets.json\") as f:\n",
    "    tickets = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "LABELS = [\"billing\", \"bug\", \"feature_request\", \"other\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "def classify(text, style):\n",
    "    system_instruction = f\"You are a support ticket classifier. Categorize the user message into one of these labels: {', '.join(LABELS)}.\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if style == \"zero_shot\":\n",
    "        prompt = f\"Classify this ticket: {text}\\nLabel:\"\n",
    "    elif style == \"few_shot\":\n",
    "        prompt = f\"\"\"Classify the following tickets:\n",
    "Ticket: I can't log in to my account.\n",
    "Label: bug\n",
    "Ticket: How much does the pro plan cost?\n",
    "Label: billing\n",
    "Ticket: I would like to have a feature to export to PDF.\n",
    "Label: feature_request\n",
    "Ticket: {text}\n",
    "Label:\"\"\"\n",
    "    elif style == \"cot\":\n",
    "        prompt = f\"\"\"Classify this ticket: {text}\n",
    "Explain your reasoning briefly, then provide the label in the format 'Label: <label>'.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = client.models.generate_content(\n",
    "        model=MODEL,\n",
    "        config={'system_instruction': system_instruction, 'temperature': 0.1},\n",
    "        contents=prompt\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    res_text = response.text.lower()\n",
    "    for label in LABELS:\n",
    "        if label in res_text.split('label:')[-1]:\n",
    "            return label\n",
    "    return \"other\"\n",
    "\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "for t in tickets:\n",
    "    row = {\"Ticket\": t[\"text\"]}\n",
    "    for style in [\"zero_shot\", \"few_shot\", \"cot\"]:\n",
    "        row[style] = classify(t[\"text\"], style)\n",
    "    results.append(row)\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
    "display(df)\n"
    ],
    "cell_type": "code"
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 3 — Structured output as a function\n",
    "\n",
    "Return JSON `{label, confidence, reason}` with low temperature, then **parse and validate** it. Handle one bad-output case. Re-run against local Ollama and compare.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def classify_structured(text, use_ollama=False):\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"Classify the following support ticket into one of {LABELS}.\n",
    "Return ONLY a JSON object with this schema:\n",
    "{{\"label\": \"billing | bug | feature_request | other\", \"confidence\": float, \"reason\": \"short string\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "Ticket: {text}\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not use_ollama:\n",
    "        # Gemini Structured Output\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            response = client.models.generate_content(\n",
    "                model=MODEL,\n",
    "                config={\n",
    "                    'temperature': 0.1,\n",
    "                    'response_mime_type': 'application/json',\n",
    "                },\n",
    "                contents=prompt\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            data = json.loads(response.text)\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"Gemini Error: {e}\")\n",
    "            return None\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Ollama / OpenAI-compatible endpoint\n",
    "        import openai\n",
    "        local_client = openai.OpenAI(base_url=\"http://localhost:11434/v1\", api_key=\"ollama\")\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            response = local_client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "                model=\"llama3.2:3b\",\n",
    "                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n",
    "                temperature=0.1,\n",
    "                response_format={ \"type\": \"json_object\" }\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            data = json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content)\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"Ollama Error: {e}\")\n",
    "            return None\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Validation\n",
    "    if data and \"label\" in data and \"confidence\" in data:\n",
    "        if data[\"label\"] in LABELS and 0 <= data[\"confidence\"] <= 1:\n",
    "            return data\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Validation failed or malformed JSON\")\n",
    "    return {\"label\": \"other\", \"confidence\": 0.0, \"reason\": \"failed validation\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"--- Gemini Structured Output ---\")\n",
    "sample_ticket = tickets[1][\"text\"] # Bug ticket\n",
    "print(f\"Ticket: {sample_ticket}\")\n",
    "print(classify_structured(sample_ticket))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n--- Ollama Structured Output (Expected to fail if Ollama not running) ---\")\n",
    "print(classify_structured(sample_ticket, use_ollama=True))\n"
    ],
    "cell_type": "code"
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Local vs hosted: did the small local model produce valid JSON as reliably?**\n",
    "\n",
    "> Gemini 2.0 Flash is extremely reliable at producing valid JSON when `response_mime_type` is set. Smaller local models like Llama 3.2:3b can sometimes struggle with complex schemas or strict JSON formatting unless specifically prompted or using a constrained decoding engine. In my experience, Gemini is more consistent, while local models may require more 'hand-holding' or multiple retries if the schema is large."
   ]
  }
